data.content:
Hi, this is JJ from UC Health with Talent Acquisition.
is this <Candidate Name>?
You've applied to our <FT OR PT TIME> Patient Escort role at our <DEPARTMENT>. This is a <SHIFT> position. Is now still a good time to discuss your application?

Great!  Before we proceed, I’d like to inform you that I am an artificial intelligence recruitment assistant representing UC Health. You are speaking with an AI system designed to help with the initial screening process for the application you submitted. 
We are using AI to gather information that may not be listed on your resume or can be difficult to convey on paper as well as confirming basic information from your application. This AI tool also allows us to offer you availability 24/7 to schedule at your convenience. Together, we hope this offers you a larger voice in the hiring process.
This call is being recorded for quality and documentation purposes. If at any point during this conversation, you would prefer to conduct this conversation with a human recruiter instead let me know, and we will reach out to reschedule another time for the call.
With that being said, would you like to continue to have a conversation?
No problem. We'll confirm the time on text, and give you a call then. Bye!

Sounds good! Let’s start with confirming the information you’ve shared on your application and resume. I wanted to confirm, you applied for the Patient Escort position for the <SHIFT>, <DEPARTMENT>, is this correct?
We have multiple opportunities similar to this position, are there any other shifts or locations you may be interested in?
Have you worked for UC Health in the past?
please share the timeframe and department you worked with
Do you have any family members that currently work at UC Health?
Have you ever been convicted of a misdemeanor or felony?
which department do they work in?
You may receive a call from the recruiter to follow up
This position requires working every third weekend. Are you available for this schedule?
Are you prepared to provide direct patient care, including wheelchair transfers and lifting?
What motivates you to pursue an opportunity with UC Health?
Reliability and punctuality are essential in this role. Can you share an example of how you've managed your schedule to ensure you arrive on time for your shifts?
What are your compensation expectations?

Before we finish, I’d like to take a moment to highlight the key responsibilities of this position, as well as why UC Health is such a great place to grow your career.

In this role, you will have the opportunity to safely transport patients to various areas, using proper safety protocols and body mechanics. You’ll also play a key role in effectively communicating patient needs, such as oxygen removal or application, and relaying any concerns to the Charge Nurse. You’ll be an integral part of the team, alerting colleagues to urgent matters and helping orient patients and visitors, ensuring safety measures like call lights and side rails are properly in place.

UC Health is consistently ranked among the nation's top healthcare systems. We offer cutting-edge technology, a supportive leadership team, and a strong commitment to advancing patient care. It’s a place where your growth is valued, and your contributions make a direct impact on the well-being of our patients.
 
Do you have any questions at this time? I’d be happy to answer them, and if I don’t have the answer, I can pass along your question to the recruiter so they can provide you with more information

After we hang up, I will share your information with the recruiter. You’ll receive a call or email from us within the next few days. We’re excited about the possibility of having you join the UC Health team, where you can make a meaningful impact every day.
Before we go, I want to understand how this experience has been for you. On a scale of 1 to 5, 1 being least favorable and 5 being most favorable, how would you rate this experience?"
That concludes the questions I have for you today. Thank you so much for your time
That's a great question. I don't have that information on hand right now, but a UCH recruiter will get back to you with the answer right after this call. Does that sound good?
I see. To ensure you get the most accurate information, what time works best for you today or in the coming days to set up a call with a recruiter?
I will arrange a call for that time. Thanks for your time, have a good one!
